obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (21315)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act, 1952.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21315&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (21316)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21316&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, "Minister" means a member of the Council of Ministers, by whatever`
  line `name called, and includes a Deputy Minister.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (21317)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Salaries and daily constituency allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 76 of 1985, s. 2, for section 3 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21317&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Salaries and daily constituency allowances.(1) Each Minister shall be entitled to receive a`
  line `salary per mensem, and an allowance for each day during the whole of his term as such Minister at the`
  line `same rates as are specified in section 3 of the Salaries, Allowances and Pension of Members of Parliament`
  line `Act, 1954 (30 of 1954) with respect to members of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Minister shall be entitled to receive a constituency allowance at the same rate as is specified`
  line `under section 8 of the said Act with respect to members of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (21318)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Residence of Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21318&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Each Minister shall be entitled without payment of rent to the use`
  line `of a furnished residence throughout his term of office and for a period of ^2[one month] immediately`
  line `thereafter, and no charge shall fall on the Minister personally in respect of the maintenance of such`
  line residence.
  line
  line `^3[(2) In the event of death of the Minister, his family shall be entitled to the use of the furnished`
  line `residence occupied by the Minister--`
  line
  line `(a) for a period of one month immediately after his death, without payment of rent and no charge`
  line `shall fall on the family of the Minister in respect of the maintenance of such residence, and`
  line
  line `(b) for a further period of one month, on payment of rent at such rates as may be prescribed by`
  line `rules made in this behalf by the Central Government and also charges in respect of electricity and`
  line `water consumed in that residence during such further period.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "residence" includes the staff quarters and other`
  line `buildings appurtenant thereto, and the garden thereof, and "maintenance" in relation to a residence`
  line `includes the payment of local rates and taxes and the provision of electricity and water.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Section 4 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 47 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "fifteen days" (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (21319)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Sumptuary allowance to Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21319&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[5. Sumptuary allowance to Ministers.There shall be paid a sumptuary allowance to each`
  line `Minister at the following rates, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Prime Minister Rupees three thousand per mensem;`
  line
  line `(b) every other Minister`
  line `who is a member of the Cabinet`
  line `Rupees two thousand per mensem;`
  line
  line `(c) a Minister of State Rupees one thousand per mensem;`
  line
  line `(d) a Deputy Minister Rupees six hundred per mensem.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the sumptuary allowance payable to each`
  line `Minister under that sub-section shall be reduced by thirty per cent. for a period of one year commencing`
  line `from the 1st April, 2020, to meet the exigencies arising out of Corona Virus (COVID-19) pandemic.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2000, s. 2, for section 5 (w.e.f. 17-9-2001).`
  line
  line `2 . Subs. by Act 44 of 2000, s. 2, for section 5 (w.e.f. 17-9-2001).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2020, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-4-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (21320)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Travelling and daily allowances to Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21320&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules made in this behalf by`
  line `the Central Government, a Minister shall be entitled to--`
  line
  line `(a) travelling allowances for himself and the members of his family and for the transport of his`
  line `and his family's effects--`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of the journey to Delhi from his usual place of residence outside Delhi for`
  line `assuming office, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of the journey from Delhi to his usual place of residence outside Delhi on`
  line `relinquishing office; and`
  line
  line `(b) travelling and daily allowances in respect of tours undertaken by him in the discharge of his`
  line `official duties, whether by sea, land or air.`
  line
  line `^1[^2[(1A) A Minister shall be entitled to an amount equal to the fare for a single journey performed`
  line `by him, during each year, within India, either alone or along with spouse or legitimate or step`
  line `children, residing with and wholly dependent on him, or any number of companions or relatives, at`
  line `the same rates at which travelling allowance is payable to such Minister under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) in respect of tours referred to in that clause, subject to a maximum of forty-eight such`
  line `fares per year:`
  line
  line `Provided that the spouse or legitimate or step children residing with and wholly dependent on the`
  line `Minister, as the case may be, may undertake such journey alone.]]`
  line
  line `(2) Any travelling allowance under this section may be paid in cash or free official transport provided`
  line `in lieu thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 76 of 1985, s. 4 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 2 of 2010, s. 2, for sub-section (1A) (w.e.f. 5-2-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (21321)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Medical treatment, etc., to Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21321&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government, a Minister and the members of his family shall be entitled free of charge to accommodation`
  line `in hospitals maintained by the Government and also to medical treatment.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (21322)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Advances to Ministers for purchase of motor-cars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21322&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `There may be paid to any Minister by way`
  line `of a repayable advance such sum of money as may be determined by rules made in this behalf for the`
  line `purchase of a motor-car in order that he may be able to discharge conveniently and efficiently the duties`
  line `of his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (21323)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Ministers not to draw salary or allowances as Members of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21323&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No person in receipt`
  line `of a salary or allowance under this Act shall be entitled to receive any sum out of funds provided by`
  line `Parliament by way of salary or allowance in respect of his membership of either House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (21324)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Notification respecting appointment, etc., of Ministers to be conclusive evidence thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21324&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The date on which any person became or ceased to be a Minister shall be published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, and any such notification shall be conclusive evidence of the fact that he became, or ceased to`
  line `be, a Minister on that date for all the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (21325)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Exemption from liability to pay income-tax on certain perquisites received by a Minister.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 76 of 1985, s. 5 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21325&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Exemption from liability to pay income-tax on certain perquisites received by a`
  line `Minister.Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), the value of`
  line `rent free furnished residence (including maintenance thereof) provided to a Minister under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 4 shall not be included in the computation of his income chargeable under the head "Salaries"`
  line `under section 15 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (21326)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 37 of 1977, s. 2, for section 11 (w.e.f. 9-12-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21326&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Power to make rules.-- (1) The Central Government may make rules to carry out the purposes`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act after the commencement of the Salaries and Allowances of`
  line `Ministers (Amendment) Act, 1977 shall be laid before each House of Parliament and no such rule shall`
  line `come into force until it has been approved, whether with or without modifications, by each House of`
  line `Parliament and published by the Central Government in the Official Gazette.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (21327)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Regularisation of certain payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21327&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `All salaries paid or payable for the period commencing`
  line `on the 14th day of May, 1952, and ending with the commencement of this Act to Ministers described as`
  line `Ministers of Cabinet rank (but not Members of the Cabinet), all charges incurred before the`
  line `commencement of this Act in respect of the accommodation provided in any hospital maintained by the`
  line `Central Government for or on the medical treatment of any Minister or any member of his family and all`
  line `payments made before such commencement by way of travelling or daily allowances to any Deputy`
  line `Minister; shall be deemed to have been properly paid, payable or incurred or made.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (21328)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976&sectionId=21328&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00006_195258_1517807327976
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal of Act 53 of 1947.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1957 (36 of 1957), s. 2 and`
  line `the First Schedule (w.e.f. 7-9-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
